        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent</hi>.</placeName>
                    <date>Oct 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. expect that the period of gestation would differ very little in the individuals of the same species, as long as its conditions of life remain the same.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> But I doubt whether it w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. serve as an absolute criterion; for although little or nothing on this head can be known with respect to species in a state of nature, yet with races of the same species, as with dogs &amp; cattle, the period is known slightly to differ. In the germination of seeds from the same capsule there is often the most wonderful &amp; inexplicable difference in the periods.</p>
<p>With my thanks for your kindness, I remain | My dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

